====== ROSEGARDEN 25.12 RELEASED ======

The Rosegarden team is proud to announce the release of version 25.12
of Rosegarden, a MIDI sequencer that features a rich understanding of
music notation along with basic support for digital audio.

  http://www.rosegardenmusic.com/

Included in this release...

===== Bug Fixes =====

  * Fix tuplet of 7 in one beat leads to incorrect durations.  Bug
    #1464.  [ffe92b80a1]
  * Fix incorrect bpm on TimeWidget.  [d94e0e096c]
  * Fix occasional unwanted recovery prompt.  Bug #1725.  [b2ed6a748d]
  * Fix stuck lilypond preview dialog.  Bug #1726.  [5857468170]
  * Fix track buttons and segment canvas getting out of sync.  Bug
    #1728.  [b06a0cee07]
  * Fix main window losing focus when mouse leaves.  Bug #1728.
    [c384771ccb]
  * Fix MIDI export problems with anacrusis and tempo changes.  Bug
    #1627.  [0683a0890d]
  * Fix undo anacrusis requiring three undos.  [c4d89ee242]
  * Fix undo for tempo changes losing ramp info.  [ea1982fdcf]
  * Fix adding and removing files in the Audio File Manager does not
    mark the document as modified.  [efc375058c]
  * Improve missing audio file handling.  Bug #1730.  [bdaf8dc014]
  * Fix audio directories being created unnecessarily.  Bug #1730.
    [f7053b39dc]
  * Fix wait cursor during audio file location dialog.  [a915292fc0]
  * Use "open directory" dialog in file location dialog instead of
    broken "file open" dialog.  Bug #1730.  [6461bc9ce4]
  * Fix unnecessary error message box.  Bug #1730.  [c6ef6415c7]
  * Fix selection problems when closing the Audio File Manager.  Bug
    #1733.  [83fa32bdb2]
  * Fix cursor not returning to normal after using audio location
    dialog.  Bug #1736.  [0d38af676e]
  * Fix sfizz plugin UI not visible.  Bug #1738.  [090f160bce]
    [f908ea2646]
  * Fix instruments refering to invalid audio inputs and submasters.
    Bug #1735.  [faa8e5186d] [722d5a2c67] [01b5e6d96f]
  * Fix LV2 crashes due to environment variables.  Bug #1737.
    [58a2e3d9fe]
  * Fix new MIDI ports called "unnamed" rather than "New Device".
    Bug #1710.  [2c18d18906]
  * Fix lilypond version issue.  Bug #1739.  [55ef24b9bf]
  * Fix Feta.xml not found message.  Bug #1741.  [d24521621d]
  * Fix "oops" message in logs.  Bug #1740.  [bb86de7422]
  * Limit mouse position in LoopRuler.  Bug #1742.  [f7216033b9]
  * Fix wrong codec selected in text codec dialog.  [6e7b2c2577]
  * Use "snap to unit" for the tools and the LoopRuler to make it
    easier to work in compound meters.  [be819c5265]
  * Add "Cursor" to "Move to Staff Above/Below" menu items.
    [a1823ca9f6]
  * Fix a crash when saving during playback.  [e835e860b3]
  * Make notation quantization color brighter.  [5bf74aee5c]
  * Fix undo after remove results in no audio in the Audio File
    Manager.  Bug #1733.  [4f732e5c17] [36a6680ed9] [ab6b89453f]
  * Fix problems when moving segments beyond composition end.
    Bug #1744.  [b3cd66b800]
  * Remove unnecessary logging.  Bug #1745.  [1cf772bf68]
  * Fix lv2 plugins not showing as lv2 plugins.  Feature Request #540.
    [83c427819c]
  * MatrixTool: Fix missing forward-decl for QKeyEvent.  Bug #1746.
    [70307ab1ee]
  * cmake: Remove X11 requirement.  Bug #1747.  [12a6aa65c9]
  * cmake: Fixed a build error.  [ff1fe47372]
  * cmake: Make gtk2 optional.  [2364f701d6]

===== New Features =====

  * Rulers now support aftertouch, both channel and key.  Feature
    Request #527.  [5ee9c807d8]
  * Rotary (knob) widget now shows label (e.g. pan) and value in its
    tooltip.  [4c42d7dc4d]
  * Snap markers to beat.  Feature Request #537.  [6c69fa3354]
  * Move markers by dragging them.  Feature Request #536.  [66b9451054]
    [00eb33ffa7] [8f334a5dbf]
  * Double-click to rename a marker.  Feature Request #535.
    [3973fdf484]
  * Edit > Select Related Segments feature.  Feature Request #534.
    [d289dc4005]
  * Audio File Manager: allow multi-select of entries in the list.
    Feature Request #533.  [2368585756]
  * Support for Akai MPK Mini IV control surface.  Patch #83.
    [35eec2215e]

===== General Improvements =====

  * Time widget rewrite and UI simplification.  [e91f8a73f0]
  * MIDI Mixer Window review and simplification.  [887e2e1d71 etc...]
  * Rotary widget (knob) review and simplification.
    [eee2941115 etc...]

====== ROSEGARDEN 25.06 RELEASED ======

The Rosegarden team is proud to announce the release of version 25.06
of Rosegarden, a MIDI sequencer that features a rich understanding of
music notation along with basic support for digital audio.

  http://www.rosegardenmusic.com/

Included in this release...

===== Bug Fixes =====

  * Lilypond: Fix the missing dot in property paths (LilyPond > 2.22).
    [3957c97969]
  * LV2: Add port sampleRate feature.  [03d35cad0a]
  * Fixed Import Studio does not create new devices.  Bug #1709.
    [4460f3521b]
  * Notation: Improve wording of highlight menu items.  Bug #1708.
    [fdc4a3553c]
  * Event Viewer: Fix editor closes when editing triggered segments.
    [baeb7bad81]
  * Fix crash when deleting a triggered segment that was being edited
    with the notation or matrix editors.  [c9cafc8ad8]
  * Fix wrong matrix editor window closed during segment split.
    Bug #1699.  [80d3e70642]
  * Handle unsaved untitled autosave.  Bug #1700.  [cef44d35e3]
  * Matrix: Fix notes not sounding across a drag select.  Bug #1697.
    [31ec6ed535]
  * Fix file dialogs forget paths.  Feature Request #518.  [5588528e46]
  * Fix crash when deleting a repeating segment opened in notation.
    Bug #1711.  [119e4672d9]
  * Fix crash on Manage MIDI Devices window close.  Debian #1091859.
    [64943ed3d8]
  * Fix crash on new document with bank editor open.  Bug #1712.
    [f68d7dbcd6]
  * Fix missing time resolution warning.  [6cbef7a786]
  * Instrument Parameters: Fix "Pan" control label cut off on the
    right.  [8a78c11ae2]
  * Fix UI locks up when hitting "Record".  Bug #1713.  [e8d16c4792]
  * Fix lyric editor with anacrusis [-1] problem.  Bug #1715.
    [82045d5ca4]
  * Fix LV2 plugin JC303 not working.  Bug #1714.  [b341fd1ce3]
  * Add JACK stop at auto stop preference.  Bug #1693.  [c86d9ca6a7]
  * Tempo And Time Signature Editor: Fix tempo time change leftovers.
    Bug #1718.  [017bdd1b60]
  * Fix potential crash when fast-forwarding or rewinding through a
    large composition while it is playing.  Bug #1717.  [01ddaca815]
  * Fix RG handling of jumping JACK transport.  Bug #1721.
    [dc2062d42e]
  * LilyPond: Fix deprecation warnings while processing RG output.
    Bug #1675.  [39bef99be1]
  * Matrix: Fix Add Tempo Change... not working.  [b9a781ee9c]
  * Fix record input connections not happening.  [38d50e757f]
  * Fix "toggle repeat" not handling mixed state in undo.  Bug #1722.
    [1128116d13]
  * Fix transport dialog time/bars not updating on Tempo and Time
    Signature changes prior to the pointer position.  [66401b64fc]
  * EventFilterDialog: Fix invalid read with "shortest" duration.
    [8068e139ba]
  * Fix LilyPond doesn't draw the repeat double bar when there are
    alternative endings.  Bug #1676.  [2e4b03092a]

===== New Features =====

  * Add an extra large track size in presentation preferences.
    Feature Request #524.  [76247e4efd]
  * Add track label width to presentation preferences.  Feature Request
    #525.  [a401a663d4]
  * EditView: Add "Edit Triggered Segment" feature.  [287a3765e1]
  * Add "Drag with dynamic modifiers (main window)" preference.
    [561db23422]
  * Constrained selection move in matrix editor.  Feature Request #298.
    [4dfb643cf5]
  * Add preference for dynamic drag.  Bug #1699.  [561db23422]
  * Add "remove all from panel" command to the Manage Controllers
    dialog Edit menu.  Feature Request #526.  [68a2373fd4]
  * RPN and NRPN editing has been added to the Event List Editor.
    Feature Request #467.  [bc567b76b3]  [0a43462bdb]
  * MIDI Export: Add RPN and NRPN support.  Feature Request #467.
    [f02f6bf8fb]
  * Event List Editor: Add filtering All On/Off button.  [42f8635286]
  * LV2: Graduate out of beta.  Enable by default.  [90fccdab0a]

===== General Improvements =====

  * The Event List Editor has been rewritten.
  * The "Edit Event" dialog has been rewritten.  This pops up when double-
    clicking on notes in Notation, the Matrix, and the Event List Editor.

===== Additional Contributions =====

